# PRD must track every product version

Whenever the app version changes (`src/lib/version.ts` `APP_VERSION`, `package.json` `version`, and `CHANGELOG`), **also update `docs/PRD.md` in the same change set**.

## Required PRD updates on each version bump

1. **Header table** — set **Status** / product version / date to the new `APP_VERSION`.
2. **Document history** — add a row for this version (what shipped that affects product requirements).
3. **Requirements / glossary / rules / routes / roadmap** — update any section that the release changed (do not leave the PRD describing old UX or obsolete rules).
4. **Shipped roadmap** — move completed items into “Shipped” with the version id.

## Do not

- Ship or commit a version bump without a corresponding PRD edit.
- Treat `docs/PRD.md` as a one-time artifact; it is living product truth.

## Version pairing

| Artifact | Must match |
|----------|------------|
| `APP_VERSION` in `src/lib/version.ts` | Product version in PRD header |
| `package.json` version | Same |
| `CHANGELOG[0]` | Summarized in PRD history + shipped notes |
| UX audit canvas (optional but recommended) | Rescore fixed vs open findings for the new version |
